* TABLE :: Number suffixes
** ( ) todo :: paucal, pluplural, collective suffixes :: create them
** DEFINITIONS and NOTES
   - paucal • a few • contextual • of sapients, most often from 2 to 5 or
     6 or 7 •
   - pluplural • a very many • of sapients, describes a crowd •
   - collective • denotes one out of the possibilities implied by the
     meaning of /collective/ •
   ---- /*examples of collective meaning*/ • a collective of people
        is a tribe, or "nation" in the sense of a (Latin) /gens/, or
        the inhabitants of a village • a collective of soldiers is an
        army • a collective of crows is a murder of crows • of deer, a
        herd •
   ---- /examples/ :: /hominen/ humans :: /hominempep/ a few humans ::
        /hominended/ a crowd or multitude of humans :: /hominâzd/
        /gens/, tribe, "nation"

        
  |------------+--------|
  | Number     | Suffix |
  |------------+--------|
  | Plural     | -en    |
  | Paucal     | -empep |
  | Pluplural  | -ended |
  | Collective | -âzd   |
  |------------+--------|

* TABLE :: Suffixes that qualify or narrow down meanings
  - RULE: these suffixes, as they modify the meaning of the base word,
    must occur only adjacent to the base word, i.e., on its
    word-border, thus creating a new base word
  - QUESTION: is the above really true? Should these be suffixed
    final particles instead, able to modify any word with attitude?
  - Question: call them attitudinals?
  - QUESTION: call only pejorative and approbative suffices
    attitudinals? and only suffix them? Or allow -pep and -ded to be
    used with verbs, adjectives, etc?
  - ( ) todo :: create approbative suffix :: answer above QUESTIONS

  |----------+--------------|
  | Function | Suffix       |
  |----------+--------------|
  | -pep     | diminutive   |
  | -ded     | augmentative |
  | -fiw     | pejorative   |
  |          | approbative  |
  |----------+--------------|

  - a

* TABLE :: numerals
  |----------+--------------|
  | Jagarôth | Arabic glyph |
  |----------+--------------|
  | zip      | 0            |
  | tot      | 1            |
  | sad      | 2            |
  | fat      | 3            |
  | fûm      | 4            |
  | kint     | 5            |
  | kor      | 6            |
  | konet    | 36           |
  | momor    | 216          |
  | stokor   | 1296         |
  |----------+--------------|

  - 2026 in senary is 13214.
  - two thousand twenty six  
  - /stokor momor-fat konet-sad kor-fûm/
  - note :: 1296 + (216*3) + (36*2) + 6 + 4
  - note :: the final 6 + 4 (/kor-fûm/) is not multiplicative like
    /momor-fat/ and /konet-sad/ are. /kor-fûm/ is additive, it means 10 (in
    decimal). one utters each digit as a multiple of 6 beginning with
    the largest multiple (/stokor/) uttered first and written on the
    left side.
  - in base-6 10000 (/stokor/) + 3000 (/momor-fat/) + 200 (/konet-sad/) +
    10 (/kor/) + 4 (/fûm/)

