* TABLE :: indirect or reported speech
  |-------------------------+------------------------------------|
  | I said, "I ate my food" | pê spelâlen weyâlen-then weyumotem |
  |                         |                                    |
  |-------------------------+------------------------------------|
  - PAST say-FINITE-1s eat-FINITE-1s-IndirectSpeech
    eat-CONCRETE-ACC-1sPossessive
  - Indirect speech is done as in Ancient Greek with /hoti/. /-then/
    is a clitic suffix indicating the word to which it is attached is
    the first word of reported speech.
  - /te/ turns that clause that follows it into an object in the
    sentence subject to grammatical processes like being in the
    Accusative or whatever.

* TABLE :: clitic suffixes, their nature and uses
  |--------+------------------------------------+-------------|
  | clitic | description                        | translation |
  |--------+------------------------------------+-------------|
  | -then  | reported speech                    | that        |
  | -thor  | non-clause conjunctive conjunction | and         |
  | -sest  | non-clause disjunctive conjunction | but         |
  |--------+------------------------------------+-------------|

* TABLE :: conjunctions, stand-alone & clitic
|-------------+-------------+-----------------------------------|
| conjunction | description | meaning                           |
|-------------+-------------+-----------------------------------|
| -then       | clitic      | marks indirect or reported speech |
| -thor       | clitic      | phrase conjunction "and"          |
| -sest       | clitic      | clause conjunction "but"          |
| koi         | word        | clausal-level "and"               |
| thrip       | word        | clausal-level "but"               |
|-------------+-------------+-----------------------------------|

